def_en: A cell is the smallest part of an animal or plant that is able to function independently. Every animal or plant is made up of millions of cells.

def_cn: 单人牢房；(修道院的)单人小室
def_en: A cell is a small room in which a prisoner is locked. A cell is also a small room in which a monk or nun lives.

def_cn: (大型组织中的)基层组织
def_en: You can refer to a small group of people within a larger organization as a cell .
